      "description": "Offering a peerless 2011 BMW M3 (E92) powered by the high-revving S65 naturally aspirated V8. This specimen is in concours-level condition, featuring a documented service history that includes preventative rod bearing replacement with VAC-coated shells and updated throttle actuators. The 6-speed manual gearbox offers precise, tactile throws, while the M-Variable differential remains silent and responsive. The chassis is structurally perfect, with no signs of subframe fatigue and factory-spec bushings throughout. Suspension dynamics are preserved via the Electronic Damper Control (EDC) system, which functions flawlessly across all damping maps. The paint depth is consistent across all panels, and the undercarriage remains free of oxidation or fluid seepage. This is a mechanically uncompromised, collector-grade example of the final naturally aspirated M3.",
